---
// src/components/chrome/DrawerTrigger.astro — M-UX T7 deliverable.
//
// Hamburger button that opens / closes the mobile drawer. Mounted
// inside `Breadcrumb.astro`'s `drawer-trigger` named slot so the
// breadcrumb's flexbox layout owns the button's placement (per
// MUX-BO-DA2-F + breakout-audit MUX-BO-ISS-04 resolution + T7 spec
// step 1 line 26 "inside `Breadcrumb.astro`'s component-internal
// drawer-trigger slot — not directly in `Base.astro`'s `breadcrumb`
// slot region").
//
// **Two-component split.** The actual drawer overlay (the aside +
// backdrop + open/close logic) lives in `Drawer.astro`, mounted at
// body level via `Base.astro`'s `slot="drawer"`. This file is
// trigger-only. See `Drawer.astro`'s header docstring for the
// rationale: a single Astro component cannot route to two parent
// slots simultaneously, but the spec + breakout audit firmly fix
// the BUTTON inside breadcrumb (so the breadcrumb's flex layout
// owns its placement) and the ASIDE at body root (so the drawer's
// `position: fixed` element escapes the sticky-breadcrumb's
// `z-index: 50` stacking context).
//
// **Communication** (per `Drawer.astro` header):
// click dispatches `cs300:drawer-toggle` CustomEvent; the sibling
// `Drawer.astro` island listens. No detail payload — toggle (open
// if closed, close if open). Same custom-event idiom as the rest
// of M3 / M-UX (`cs300:read-status-changed`, `cs300:annotation-
// added`, `cs300:toc-read-status-painted`).
//
// **Visibility gate** (T7 spec step 1 line 26 + step 16 "Hamburger
// visible only at <1024px"): the @media (max-width: 1023.98px)
// rule on the button itself flips display from `none` to
// `inline-flex`. At ≥1024px the button is removed from layout AND
// from the tab order so keyboard users at desktop don't reach a
// dead trigger.
//
// **Accessibility** (T7 spec step 7):
//   - `aria-controls="drawer"` ties the button to the aside.
//   - `aria-expanded` reflects open state — toggled by Drawer.astro
//     in its open() / close() functions.
//   - `aria-label="Open navigation"` reads as a friendly name for
//     screen readers (the visible glyph is the three-bar icon ☰).
//   - `id="drawer-trigger"` is the focus-restore target on close
//     (Drawer.astro's lastFocused fallback).
//
// Companion files:
//   - design_docs/milestones/m_ux_polish/tasks/T7_mobile_drawer.md
//   - src/components/chrome/Drawer.astro (T7 sibling — the overlay)
//   - src/components/chrome/Breadcrumb.astro (T3 — drawer-trigger
//     slot host)
---

<button
  type="button"
  id="drawer-trigger"
  class="drawer-trigger"
  aria-controls="drawer"
  aria-expanded="false"
  aria-label="Open navigation"
>
  <span class="drawer-trigger-icon" aria-hidden="true">☰</span>
</button>

<style>
  /* Tokens come from src/styles/chrome.css (imported globally by
     Base.astro). */
  .drawer-trigger {
    /* Hidden at desktop — drawer affordance is mobile-only. The
       1024px breakpoint matches `Base.astro`'s grid breakpoint
       (chrome.css `--mux-bp-desktop`). 1023.98px keeps the rule
       tight against the desktop boundary so a viewport at exactly
       1024px gets the desktop layout. */
    display: none;
    appearance: none;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--mux-border-subtle);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: var(--mux-space-1) var(--mux-space-2);
    color: var(--mux-fg);
    cursor: pointer;
    line-height: 1;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .drawer-trigger:hover {
    background: var(--mux-surface-alt);
  }

  .drawer-trigger:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--mux-accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .drawer-trigger-icon {
    display: inline-block;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1023.98px) {
    .drawer-trigger {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  /**
   * Trigger script — emits `cs300:drawer-toggle` on click. The
   * Drawer.astro island catches the event and runs the open/close
   * logic. Inline `<script>` so the trigger is interactive on first
   * paint; matches the rest of M-UX/M3's no-framework JS island
   * pattern.
   */
  const trigger = document.getElementById('drawer-trigger');
  trigger?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('cs300:drawer-toggle'));
  });
</script>
